# 🔥 BROWSER RECOVERY — Auto-Cleanup Protocol (MDC)

> Loaded automatically when Cursor detects cleanup-related context.

## Immediate Actions (In This Order)

### 1. Kill ALL Browser Processes
```bash
pkill -9 -f "chromium" 2>/dev/null || true
pkill -9 -f "chrome.*remote-debugging" 2>/dev/null || true
pkill -9 -f "chrome.*--automation" 2>/dev/null || true
sleep 1
```

### 2. Delete ALL Recordings (Current Conversation)
```bash
CONV_DIR=~/.gemini/antigravity/brain/<CONVERSATION_ID>
find "$CONV_DIR" -name "*.webp" -delete 2>/dev/null
find "$CONV_DIR" -name "*.webp.gz" -delete 2>/dev/null
```

### 3. Clean Screenshots & Temp Media
```bash
CONV_DIR=~/.gemini/antigravity/brain/<CONVERSATION_ID>
find "$CONV_DIR" -name "*.png" -delete 2>/dev/null
rm -rf "$CONV_DIR"/.tempmediaStorage 2>/dev/null
rm -rf "$CONV_DIR"/.system_generated/click_feedback 2>/dev/null
```

### 4. Clear Browser Caches
```bash
rm -rf ~/.cache/ms-playwright/chromium-*/Cache 2>/dev/null
rm -rf /tmp/.org.chromium.Chromium.* 2>/dev/null
```

### 5. Report
```bash
echo "Artifacts dir: $(du -sh ~/.gemini/antigravity 2>/dev/null | cut -f1)"
echo "Chrome procs: $(pgrep -c -f 'chromium|chrome' 2>/dev/null || echo '0')"
echo "Available RAM: $(free -h | awk '/Mem:/ {print $7}')"
```
